  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to always have a mailserver selected so that I can continue receiving expired messages, even when installing a new build which contains mailservers with different IDs.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Currently the mailserver selection is saved by ID. When the default mailserver IDs are changed, the app shows the list with no selection. When we try to restore a mailserver and the ID is not found, we should execute the random selection logic again.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n\r\n- I install a new build which has different IDs for the mailservers\r\n- When I open the mailserver list in Profile, a new mailserver has been selected\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\n- I install a new build which has different IDs for the mailservers\r\n- When I open the mailserver list in Profile, no mailserver is selected",
